	E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report by {{articleAuthors}} entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> <a href="{{articleDoi}}" data-mce-href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>. As a reminder, the review due date is {{reviewDueDate}}. If you are unable to meet this deadline, we would be very grateful if you could us know by replying to this email. Otherwise, many thanks in advance for writing your review.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p><p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p><p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p><p>or</p><p>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p><p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p><p>Guidelines for reviewers of Registered Reports can be found <a href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" data-mce-href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers">here</a>, including <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357">specific tips for reviewing effectively</a>.</p><p>Thank you in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. Reviewers are vital to 